name="source">Definition 4.6 of <fr:link
href="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh.xml"
type="local"
addr="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh">Blechschmidt</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>\mathbb {T}</fr:tex> be a geometric theory and let <fr:tex>U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex> be its generic model in <fr:tex>\mathbf {Set} { \mathopen {} \left  [ \mathbb {T} \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. The <fr:em>spectrum</fr:em> of a <fr:tex>U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex>-algebra <fr:tex>M</fr:tex> is the set of <fr:tex>U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex>-algebra homomorphisms <fr:tex>M \to U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex>. (Recall that a <fr:tex>U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex>-algebra is a model of <fr:tex>\mathbb {T}</fr:tex> equipped with a homomorphism from <fr:tex>U_{ \mathbb {T} }</fr:tex>.)</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
